<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ871218-0035 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief:Nerco Inc.</HL><DD> 12/18/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> PPW NERNATURAL GAS, PIPELINES (LNG)PETROLEUM (PET)TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM) </IN><TEXT>   Nerco Inc., Portland, Ore., said it bought interests in 27 southern Louisiana oil and gas wells and certain undeveloped properties from a group of Louisiana investors.    The mining and resource-development concern didn't disclose terms of the agreement. But a spokesman noted that the purchase is Nerco's fourth major Louisiana oil and gas acquisition this year, with the total investment &quot;more than $50 million&quot; for the year.    Nerco's stakes in the the wells range from 2% to 60%. Proven developed and undeveloped reserves in the most recent acquisition total an estimated 13.6 billion cubic feet of natural gas and 675,000 barrels of oil, Nerco said.    Nerco is 90%-owned by PacifiCorp, a utility holding company also based in Portland. As previously reported, Nerco recently agreed in principle with Middle South Utilities Inc.'s Louisiana Power andamp; Light unit to replace an existing coal contract with a 25-year natural gas supply arrangement. </TEXT></DOC>